    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>It would be possible to combine χόρτος[b] ({D:3.48}) with χόρτος[a] small plant, grass ({D:3.15}), since the meaning of χόρτος[a] would seem to include the meaning of sprout. On the other hand, the semantic focus of {S:04100402800012} appears to be upon the tender sprout, rather than upon the full-size plant, and since this distinction is lexically important in a number of languages, the term χόρτος has been divided into χόρτος[a] and χόρτος[b] .</Content>
    </Note>
  </Notes>
